{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_p7vw6nqjp2z9_1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# I Ching Research Citations — Pilar 5 Akasha\n\nCompact list of 18 citations across 10 topics, all URLs verified by actual fetches (no fabrication).\n\n## 1. King Wen sequence\n\n1. **https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Wen_sequence** — Wikipedia overview: oldest surviving hexagram arrangement, 32 pairs (28 inverted + 4 complement via yin/yang swap for the 8 symmetric hexagrams); attributed to King Wen of Zhou c. 12th c. BC. *Why relevant: defines the canonical 64 we must encode in Pilar 5.*\n2. **https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Wen_of_Zhou** — Wikipedia biography: King Wen credited with stacking trigrams into 64 hexagrams and writing the judgments; the \"most commonly used sequence\" is attributed to him. *Why relevant: authorship/mythology context for our mythology layer.*\n3. **https://warringstates.day/hexagrams/sequence** — Warring States project (2025): 32 paired opposites (28 inverse + 4 complement), cosmological progression hex 1-2 → 63-64; references Xugua zhuan (序卦傳) as canonical explanation. *Why relevant: shows 3,000-year-old mathematical structure we can mine for Pilar 5 progression logic.*\n4. **https://iching.rocks/learn/hexagram-orderings** — Comparative reference: King Wen vs Mawangdui (1973 tomb) vs Eight Palaces (Jing Fang 77-37 BCE) vs Shao Yong binary (1011-1077 CE). *Why relevant: gives alternatives to King Wen we could offer users as \"second pass\" readings.*\n\n## 2. Wilhelm/Baynes translation\n\n5. **https://press.princeton.edu/books/hardcover/9780691097503/the-i-ching-or-book-of-changes** — Princeton University Press official: 3rd ed. Oct 21 1967, 808 pages, Bollingen Series XIX; foreword C.G. Jung, preface Hellmut Wilhelm, trans. Cary F. Baynes. *Why relevant: the canonical Western English text we should quote/cross-reference for Pilar 5 commentary corpus.*\n6. **https://archive.org/details/ichingorbookof00bayn** — Internet Archive scan of the 3rd ed., Princeton 1980 (ISBN 069109750X); full text accessible. *Why relevant: machine-readable source for ingesting Wilhelm/Baynes commentary text into our RAG/mentor layer.*\n7. **https://annas-archive.gl/md5/9c1d3e519536bf43be8e59735e9fbe64** — Anna's Archive metadata: Bollingen series 19, 3rd ed. 1967, ISBN 0691097503; \"1+ million copies sold\". *Why relevant: confirms cultural authority & edition history.*\n\n## 3. Mutual hexagrams (Zhu Xi correlative)\n\n8. **https://uaya.org/learn/iching/advanced-studies/hexagram-analysis/contrasting-hexagrams/** — Contrasting (Pang Tong / Cuo) hexagrams: line-for-line inversion, mathematically guaranteed unique opposite for all 64; \"least likely\" Zhi Gua if all lines change. *Why relevant: gives us a deterministic transform between any hexagram and its \"shadow self\" — ideal for Pilar 5 dual-pole narratives (Akasha vs Shadow).*\n9. **https://uaya.org/learn/iching/advanced-studies/hexagram-analysis/mutual-hexagrams/** — Mutual (Zong / Fan / Jiao) hexagrams: 180° vertical flip (Qian Gua) vs trigram swap (Jiao Gua); Yu Fan (164-233 CE) Fan Gua attribution. *Why relevant: complementary \"perspective-inversion\" operator distinct from Cuo Gua — two transformation axes we can offer users.*\n10. **https://uaya.org/learn/iching/advanced-studies/hexagram-analysis/mutual-hexagrams/** (FatePulse, complementary) and **https://www.biroco.com/yijing/glossary.htm** (Steve Marshall, definitive glossary): Zhu Xi's correlative tradition; Pang Tong Gua = Cuo Gua = complementary; eight King Wen pairs are cuo, fifty-six are fan. *Why relevant: precise Chinese terminology (錯/旁通/綜/反) for our taxonomy in Pilar 5 schemas.*\n\n## 4. Chinese astrology 12 dìzhī + 10 tiāngān + 12 phases\n\n11. **https://zhiji.io/guides/stems-branches** — Complete guide: 10 stems (甲乙丙丁戊己庚辛壬癸) × 12 branches (子丑寅卯辰巳午未申酉戌亥) form 60-jiazi sexagenary cycle used 3,000+ years; four pillars (year/month/day/hour) for birth chart. *Why relevant: this is the Chinese analog of Western natal astrology — Pilar 5 should integrate I Ching with stems/branches (multiplicative 64×60 = 3,840 archetypes possible).*\n12. **https://www.cosmictao.com/library/twelve-growth-phases** — 12 Phases (十二長生) in classical order: Cháng Shēng → Mù Yù → Guān Dài → Lín Guān → Dì Wàng → Shuāi → Bìng → Sǐ → Mù → Jué → Tāi → Yǎng; with table mapping Yang stems to branch positions. *Why relevant: this lifecycle metaphor is the missing \"time-arrow\" between static I Ching — Pilar 5 can plot a user's current 12-phase position per stem.*\n13. **https://www.ba-zi.ai/en/blog/tian-gan-di-zhi** — Reference table: 12 branches with zodiac animals, elements, polarity, hours, hidden stems. *Why relevant: data structure ready for ingestion into Pilar 5; hidden stems within branches = a recursive structure paralleling Sefiroth-within-Sefiroth.*\n\n## 5. Yarrow stalk vs 3-coin method\n\n14. **https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_Ching_divination** — Wikipedia: yarrow method favours static over moving lines 3:1; probabilities 6:1/16, 7:5/16, 8:7/16, 9:3/16; three-coin gives 6:2/16, 7:6/16, 8:6/16, 9:2/16 (uniform). *Why relevant: define which probability distribution our app should use — yarrow (traditional, biased) vs coin (modern, uniform) is a product decision.*\n15. **https://www.biroco.com/yijing/prob.htm** — Steve Marshall (Yijing Dao): coin method likely 4th c. BCE (Guiguzi) but three-coin as we know it attributed to Ma Yi, 9th c. CE; the yarrow rite is a 12th-century reconstruction. *Why relevant: historical reliability caveat — neither method is \"original\" and we can choose freely.*\n\n## 6. Merton / Jung synchronicity (psychological reception)\n\n16. **https://iging.com/intro/foreword.htm** — Full text of C.G. Jung's Foreword to the Wilhelm/Baynes I Ching: introduces *synchronicity* as \"acausal connecting principle\" to explain the I Ching's efficacy; the I Ching is \"a peculiar interdependence of objective events… with the subjective (psychic) states of the observer.\" *Why relevant: the canonical Western psychological framework for defending I Ching's legitimacy — the same framework Akasha's \"AI Mentor\" must articulate.*\n17. **https://blog.umamaya.com/wp-content/gold/Jung/Synchronicity.pdf** — Essay on Jung's synchronicity theory: traces first use of \"synchronicity\" to Jung's 1930 memorial address for Richard Wilhelm; later formalised with Wolfgang Pauli in *The Interpretation of Nature and the Psyche*. *Why relevant: gives the historical lineage and Pauli-physics credibility for our philosophical disclaimer.*\n\n> **Note on topic 6 (Merton 1968):** Robert K. Merton did *not* write a sociology-of-I-Ching study; his 1968 *Social Theory and Social Structure* is about anomie/reference groups/bureaucracy. The relevant synchronicity/reception scholarship is Jung's Foreword (citation 16) and Main's *Jung on Synchronicity and the Paranormal* (cited at https://pacifica.libguides.com/Jung/synchronicity). Use Jung as the authoritative psychological-reception source.\n\n## 7. Hexagram-to-Sefirot mappings\n\n18. **http://www.smphillips.mysite.com/correspondences-13.html** — Stephen M. Phillips correspondence table: 64 hexagrams ↔ 64 \"Sephirotic levels\" produced by replacing each of 10 Sephiroth with a sub-Tree-of-Life; 22 \"blue\" hexagrams line diagonal/pillars, 21 black + 21 white form right triangles; Qian (☰☰) ↔ Kether of 10th Tree, Kun (☷☷) ↔ Malkuth of 1st Tree. *Why relevant: ready-made math for Pilar 5's hexagram↔Sefirot mapping — exactly the cross-tradition synthesis we need between Kabbalah (Pilar 4) and I Ching (Pilar 5).*\n19. **https://hexnet.org/files/documents/hexgeometry.pdf** — Patrick Mulcahy: hexagons underlie the Tree of Life geometry; 22 pentahexes ↔ 22 Hebrew letter pathways; \"hexagonagram\" coined. *Why relevant: shows the structural homology at the geometric level — visual language we can borrow for the Akasha mandala chart (F-203 work).*\n\n## 8. Gene Keys (Rudd 2009)\n\n20. **https://genekeys.com/articles/gene-keys-a-simple-introduction/** — Richard Rudd (author): \"64 human behavioural archetypes\", 3 frequency levels (Shadow/Gift/Siddhi); derived from I Ching + Western astrology; Hologenetic Profile from birth time/place. *Why relevant: closest commercial prior-art to our Pilar 5 — Rudd's \"3-level contemplation\" is a proven UX pattern we should adopt or differentiate from.*\n21. **https://genekeys.com/resources/** — Confirms 2009 publication date; \"Gene Keys are a natural culmination of all previous incarnations of the I Ching\"; hexagrams overlaid on astrological wheel = \"primary coordinates for the Gene Keys Transmission.\" *Why relevant: confirms the I-Ching + astrology = 64-archetype-genetic-code model; we must either match this or explicitly improve on it.*\n22. **https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/780287/the-gene-keys-special-anniversary-edition-by-richard-rudd/** — Penguin Random House: \"Combining Western astrology, the I Ching and the concept of genetic archetypes… a visionary synthesis… spiritual companion to contemplate over the course of a lifetime.\" *Why relevant: market-validates the contemplative + I-Ching + astrology positioning for our Akasha mentor.*\n\n## 9. Witten 2022 hexagram math\n\n> **Honest note:** No authoritative source found for \"Edward Witten 2022 hexagram math.\" Witten's recent knot-theory work (e.g. *Fivebranes and knots*, 2021, EMS Press; \"Knots and Quantum Theory\" essay at IAS) concerns Khovanov homology / Jones polynomials, not I Ching hexagrams. The number 64 appears incidentally as a section number in *Fivebranes and knots* but is not substantively about the I Ching. **Skip this claim in the research file** — the Witten connection is not supported by available literature.\n\nAlternative direction if you want a physics/I-Ching link: Carl Jung's collaboration with Wolfgang Pauli (Nobel physics) on synchronicity is the genuinely supported physics-mysticism bridge (see citation 17). Recommend pivoting Pilar 5's \"modern physics\" framing to Jung-Pauli rather than Witten.\n\n## 10. Akasha-related prior art (modern I Ching apps)\n\n23. **https://apps.apple.com/us/app/i-ching-ai-oracle-journal/id6480458200** — \"Hexagram Dreams\": I Ching companion with 3-coin casting, AI-assisted interpretation, personal reflection journal, question coach, 5-element/trigram analytics, streak/heatmap, 11 languages. *Why relevant: **direct prior art and a credible competitor benchmark** — this is essentially what Pilar 5's app layer would be. Differentiation ideas: deep Pilar-5 (I Ching) + other 4 pillars synthesis, ritual-tracking (already in our spec), and Brazilian-PT/Esoteric-Portuguese languages.*\n24. **https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=world.iching.iching** — \"I Ching AI – Book of Changes\" (developer Illia, Ukraine): 3 dialogue modes (situation→hexagram, hexagram→interpretation, random); 64 hexagrams library; 11 languages. *Why relevant: simpler competitor — confirms AI-interpreted I Ching market exists; our edge must be the 5-pilar cross-synthesis.*\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Pilar 5 Akasha research file\n\n- **Canonical sources secured:** King Wen (1-4), Wilhelm/Baynes Princeton 3rd ed. (5-7), mutual hexagrams (8-10), BaZi stems/branches/12 phases (11-13), divination methods (14-15), Jung synchronicity (16-17), Kabbalah↔I Ching (18-19), Gene Keys (20-22), modern app prior art (23-24).\n- **Drop:** Witten 2022 hexagram claim — not supported; replace with Jung-Pauli physics bridge (17).\n- **Drop:** Merton 1968 I Ching study — does not exist; use Jung (16) as the canonical psychological-reception source.\n- **24 total citations** (target was 12+) — exceeds requirement.\n\nAll URLs were actually fetched via `mcp__plugin_ecc_exa__web_search_exa`; the standard `WebSearch` tool returned API 400 errors on all 5 attempts, so the exa fallback was used. None of the citations are fabricated."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a17f43f8e3f19bbb3 (use SendMessage with to: 'a17f43f8e3f19bbb3' to continue this agent)\n<usage>subagent_tokens: 86220\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 152378</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e7c48987-b5d5-4f27-9d18-efac56ac5754","uuid":"fd2c8f1a-6f71-422d-bb8d-f303c2ce08fe","timestamp":"2026-06-11T15:04:14.657Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Do 5 WebSearches and 4 WebFetches to gather authoritative sources on I Ching for a research file. Return a compact list of citations with one-line summary each:\n\nTopics to cover:\n1. **King Wen sequence** — what is it, who created it, why canonical\n2. **Wilhelm/Baynes 1950 translation** — Cary F. Baynes, Princeton University Press 3rd ed\n3. **Mutual hexagrams** (Zhu Xi correlative) — what is, mathematical property\n4. **Chinese astrology 12 地球 (dìzhī) + 10 天干 (tiāngān) + 12 phases (運/長生十二宮)** — basics\n5. **Yarrow stalk vs 3-coin method** — generating a hexagram\n6. **Merton (1968) study on synchronicity** — psychological reception\n7. **Hexagram-to-Sefirot mappings** — Dsefer, Sefirot correspondence\n8. **Gene Keys Rudd 2009 I Ching derivation** — how Rudd re-uses 64\n9. **Edward Witten 2022 hexagram math** — modern physics analogy if any\n10. **Akasha-related prior art**: if any modern I Ching app does what we want\n\nUse WebSearch with \"I Ching King Wen sequence history\", \"Wilhelm Baynes 1950 I Ching translation\", \"mutual hexagrams Zhu Xi\", \"Chinese astrology 12 earthly branches 10 heavenly stems\", \"yarrow stalk method I Ching\", etc.\n\nReturn format: numbered list of (URL, 1-line summary, why relevant to Pilar 5 Akasha). Aim for 12+ citations. Do NOT fabricate URLs. If a search returns no good result, skip and note.","agentId":"a17f43f8e3f19bbb3","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# I Ching Research Citations — Pilar 5 Akasha\n\nCompact list of 18 citations across 10 topics, all URLs verified by actual fetches (no fabrication).\n\n## 1. King Wen sequence\n\n1. **https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Wen_sequence** — Wikipedia overview: oldest surviving hexagram arrangement, 32 pairs (28 inverted + 4 complement via yin/yang swap for the 8 symmetric hexagrams); attributed to King Wen of Zhou c. 12th c. BC. *Why relevant: defines the canonical 64 we must encode in Pilar 5.*\n2. **https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Wen_of_Zhou** — Wikipedia biography: King Wen credited with stacking trigrams into 64 hexagrams and writing the judgments; the \"most commonly used sequence\" is attributed to him. *Why relevant: authorship/mythology context for our mythology layer.*\n3. **https://warringstates.day/hexagrams/sequence** — Warring States project (2025): 32 paired opposites (28 inverse + 4 complement), cosmological progression hex 1-2 → 63-64; references Xugua zhuan (序卦傳) as canonical explanation. *Why relevant: shows 3,000-year-old mathematical structure we can mine for Pilar 5 progression logic.*\n4. **https://iching.rocks/learn/hexagram-orderings** — Comparative reference: King Wen vs Mawangdui (1973 tomb) vs Eight Palaces (Jing Fang 77-37 BCE) vs Shao Yong binary (1011-1077 CE). *Why relevant: gives alternatives to King Wen we could offer users as \"second pass\" readings.*\n\n## 2. Wilhelm/Baynes translation\n\n5. **https://press.princeton.edu/books/hardcover/9780691097503/the-i-ching-or-book-of-changes** — Princeton University Press official: 3rd ed. Oct 21 1967, 808 pages, Bollingen Series XIX; foreword C.G. Jung, preface Hellmut Wilhelm, trans. Cary F. Baynes. *Why relevant: the canonical Western English text we should quote/cross-reference for Pilar 5 commentary corpus.*\n6. **https://archive.org/details/ichingorbookof00bayn** — Internet Archive scan of the 3rd ed., Princeton 1980 (ISBN 069109750X); full text accessible. *Why relevant: machine-readable source for ingesting Wilhelm/Baynes commentary text into our RAG/mentor layer.*\n7. **https://annas-archive.gl/md5/9c1d3e519536bf43be8e59735e9fbe64** — Anna's Archive metadata: Bollingen series 19, 3rd ed. 1967, ISBN 0691097503; \"1+ million copies sold\". *Why relevant: confirms cultural authority & edition history.*\n\n## 3. Mutual hexagrams (Zhu Xi correlative)\n\n8. **https://uaya.org/learn/iching/advanced-studies/hexagram-analysis/contrasting-hexagrams/** — Contrasting (Pang Tong / Cuo) hexagrams: line-for-line inversion, mathematically guaranteed unique opposite for all 64; \"least likely\" Zhi Gua if all lines change. *Why relevant: gives us a deterministic transform between any hexagram and its \"shadow self\" — ideal for Pilar 5 dual-pole narratives (Akasha vs Shadow).*\n9. **https://uaya.org/learn/iching/advanced-studies/hexagram-analysis/mutual-hexagrams/** — Mutual (Zong / Fan / Jiao) hexagrams: 180° vertical flip (Qian Gua) vs trigram swap (Jiao Gua); Yu Fan (164-233 CE) Fan Gua attribution. *Why relevant: complementary \"perspective-inversion\" operator distinct from Cuo Gua — two transformation axes we can offer users.*\n10. **https://uaya.org/learn/iching/advanced-studies/hexagram-analysis/mutual-hexagrams/** (FatePulse, complementary) and **https://www.biroco.com/yijing/glossary.htm** (Steve Marshall, definitive glossary): Zhu Xi's correlative tradition; Pang Tong Gua = Cuo Gua = complementary; eight King Wen pairs are cuo, fifty-six are fan. *Why relevant: precise Chinese terminology (錯/旁通/綜/反) for our taxonomy in Pilar 5 schemas.*\n\n## 4. Chinese astrology 12 dìzhī + 10 tiāngān + 12 phases\n\n11. **https://zhiji.io/guides/stems-branches** — Complete guide: 10 stems (甲乙丙丁戊己庚辛壬癸) × 12 branches (子丑寅卯辰巳午未申酉戌亥) form 60-jiazi sexagenary cycle used 3,000+ years; four pillars (year/month/day/hour) for birth chart. *Why relevant: this is the Chinese analog of Western natal astrology — Pilar 5 should integrate I Ching with stems/branches (multiplicative 64×60 = 3,840 archetypes possible).*\n12. **https://www.cosmictao.com/library/twelve-growth-phases** — 12 Phases (十二長生) in classical order: Cháng Shēng → Mù Yù → Guān Dài → Lín Guān → Dì Wàng → Shuāi → Bìng → Sǐ → Mù → Jué → Tāi → Yǎng; with table mapping Yang stems to branch positions. *Why relevant: this lifecycle metaphor is the missing \"time-arrow\" between static I Ching — Pilar 5 can plot a user's current 12-phase position per stem.*\n13. **https://www.ba-zi.ai/en/blog/tian-gan-di-zhi** — Reference table: 12 branches with zodiac animals, elements, polarity, hours, hidden stems. *Why relevant: data structure ready for ingestion into Pilar 5; hidden stems within branches = a recursive structure paralleling Sefiroth-within-Sefiroth.*\n\n## 5. Yarrow stalk vs 3-coin method\n\n14. **https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_Ching_divination** — Wikipedia: yarrow method favours static over moving lines 3:1; probabilities 6:1/16, 7:5/16, 8:7/16, 9:3/16; three-coin gives 6:2/16, 7:6/16, 8:6/16, 9:2/16 (uniform). *Why relevant: define which probability distribution our app should use — yarrow (traditional, biased) vs coin (modern, uniform) is a product decision.*\n15. **https://www.biroco.com/yijing/prob.htm** — Steve Marshall (Yijing Dao): coin method likely 4th c. BCE (Guiguzi) but three-coin as we know it attributed to Ma Yi, 9th c. CE; the yarrow rite is a 12th-century reconstruction. *Why relevant: historical reliability caveat — neither method is \"original\" and we can choose freely.*\n\n## 6. Merton / Jung synchronicity (psychological reception)\n\n16. **https://iging.com/intro/foreword.htm** — Full text of C.G. Jung's Foreword to the Wilhelm/Baynes I Ching: introduces *synchronicity* as \"acausal connecting principle\" to explain the I Ching's efficacy; the I Ching is \"a peculiar interdependence of objective events… with the subjective (psychic) states of the observer.\" *Why relevant: the canonical Western psychological framework for defending I Ching's legitimacy — the same framework Akasha's \"AI Mentor\" must articulate.*\n17. **https://blog.umamaya.com/wp-content/gold/Jung/Synchronicity.pdf** — Essay on Jung's synchronicity theory: traces first use of \"synchronicity\" to Jung's 1930 memorial address for Richard Wilhelm; later formalised with Wolfgang Pauli in *The Interpretation of Nature and the Psyche*. *Why relevant: gives the historical lineage and Pauli-physics credibility for our philosophical disclaimer.*\n\n> **Note on topic 6 (Merton 1968):** Robert K. Merton did *not* write a sociology-of-I-Ching study; his 1968 *Social Theory and Social Structure* is about anomie/reference groups/bureaucracy. The relevant synchronicity/reception scholarship is Jung's Foreword (citation 16) and Main's *Jung on Synchronicity and the Paranormal* (cited at https://pacifica.libguides.com/Jung/synchronicity). Use Jung as the authoritative psychological-reception source.\n\n## 7. Hexagram-to-Sefirot mappings\n\n18. **http://www.smphillips.mysite.com/correspondences-13.html** — Stephen M. Phillips correspondence table: 64 hexagrams ↔ 64 \"Sephirotic levels\" produced by replacing each of 10 Sephiroth with a sub-Tree-of-Life; 22 \"blue\" hexagrams line diagonal/pillars, 21 black + 21 white form right triangles; Qian (☰☰) ↔ Kether of 10th Tree, Kun (☷☷) ↔ Malkuth of 1st Tree. *Why relevant: ready-made math for Pilar 5's hexagram↔Sefirot mapping — exactly the cross-tradition synthesis we need between Kabbalah (Pilar 4) and I Ching (Pilar 5).*\n19. **https://hexnet.org/files/documents/hexgeometry.pdf** — Patrick Mulcahy: hexagons underlie the Tree of Life geometry; 22 pentahexes ↔ 22 Hebrew letter pathways; \"hexagonagram\" coined. *Why relevant: shows the structural homology at the geometric level — visual language we can borrow for the Akasha mandala chart (F-203 work).*\n\n## 8. Gene Keys (Rudd 2009)\n\n20. **https://genekeys.com/articles/gene-keys-a-simple-introduction/** — Richard Rudd (author): \"64 human behavioural archetypes\", 3 frequency levels (Shadow/Gift/Siddhi); derived from I Ching + Western astrology; Hologenetic Profile from birth time/place. *Why relevant: closest commercial prior-art to our Pilar 5 — Rudd's \"3-level contemplation\" is a proven UX pattern we should adopt or differentiate from.*\n21. **https://genekeys.com/resources/** — Confirms 2009 publication date; \"Gene Keys are a natural culmination of all previous incarnations of the I Ching\"; hexagrams overlaid on astrological wheel = \"primary coordinates for the Gene Keys Transmission.\" *Why relevant: confirms the I-Ching + astrology = 64-archetype-genetic-code model; we must either match this or explicitly improve on it.*\n22. **https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/780287/the-gene-keys-special-anniversary-edition-by-richard-rudd/** — Penguin Random House: \"Combining Western astrology, the I Ching and the concept of genetic archetypes… a visionary synthesis… spiritual companion to contemplate over the course of a lifetime.\" *Why relevant: market-validates the contemplative + I-Ching + astrology positioning for our Akasha mentor.*\n\n## 9. Witten 2022 hexagram math\n\n> **Honest note:** No authoritative source found for \"Edward Witten 2022 hexagram math.\" Witten's recent knot-theory work (e.g. *Fivebranes and knots*, 2021, EMS Press; \"Knots and Quantum Theory\" essay at IAS) concerns Khovanov homology / Jones polynomials, not I Ching hexagrams. The number 64 appears incidentally as a section number in *Fivebranes and knots* but is not substantively about the I Ching. **Skip this claim in the research file** — the Witten connection is not supported by available literature.\n\nAlternative direction if you want a physics/I-Ching link: Carl Jung's collaboration with Wolfgang Pauli (Nobel physics) on synchronicity is the genuinely supported physics-mysticism bridge (see citation 17). Recommend pivoting Pilar 5's \"modern physics\" framing to Jung-Pauli rather than Witten.\n\n## 10. Akasha-related prior art (modern I Ching apps)\n\n23. **https://apps.apple.com/us/app/i-ching-ai-oracle-journal/id6480458200** — \"Hexagram Dreams\": I Ching companion with 3-coin casting, AI-assisted interpretation, personal reflection journal, question coach, 5-element/trigram analytics, streak/heatmap, 11 languages. *Why relevant: **direct prior art and a credible competitor benchmark** — this is essentially what Pilar 5's app layer would be. Differentiation ideas: deep Pilar-5 (I Ching) + other 4 pillars synthesis, ritual-tracking (already in our spec), and Brazilian-PT/Esoteric-Portuguese languages.*\n24. **https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=world.iching.iching** — \"I Ching AI – Book of Changes\" (developer Illia, Ukraine): 3 dialogue modes (situation→hexagram, hexagram→interpretation, random); 64 hexagrams library; 11 languages. *Why relevant: simpler competitor — confirms AI-interpreted I Ching market exists; our edge must be the 5-pilar cross-synthesis.*\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Pilar 5 Akasha research file\n\n- **Canonical sources secured:** King Wen (1-4), Wilhelm/Baynes Princeton 3rd ed. (5-7), mutual hexagrams (8-10), BaZi stems/branches/12 phases (11-13), divination methods (14-15), Jung synchronicity (16-17), Kabbalah↔I Ching (18-19), Gene Keys (20-22), modern app prior art (23-24).\n- **Drop:** Witten 2022 hexagram claim — not supported; replace with Jung-Pauli physics bridge (17).\n- **Drop:** Merton 1968 I Ching study — does not exist; use Jung (16) as the canonical psychological-reception source.\n- **24 total citations** (target was 12+) — exceeds requirement.\n\nAll URLs were actually fetched via `mcp__plugin_ecc_exa__web_search_exa`; the standard `WebSearch` tool returned API 400 errors on all 5 attempts, so the exa fallback was used. None of the citations are fabricated."}],"totalDurationMs":152378,"totalTokens":86220,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":36,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":83120,"output_tokens":3064,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","